  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 112 g
  sugar: 24 g
  protein: 18 g
  fiber: 14 g
  sodium: 1780 mg
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
time required: 25 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/southwest-black-bean-messy-janes-627169a18000aa54e50dba71
cuisine: Mexican
---

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Red Onion{1/2}; finely chop remaining @Red Onion{1/2}(chopped). Zest and quarter @Lime{1}. Drain @Corn Kernels{13.4%ounce}. Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{2%clove}.

In a small #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine sliced onion, juice from half the lime, @Sugar{1/2%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{}; cover bowl tightly with #plastic wrap{} and microwave until onion is bright pink, ~{30%seconds}. Set aside to pickle, tossing occasionally, until ready to serve.

In a second small #bowl{}, combine @Tex-Mex Paste{1%unit}, @Ketchup{2%tablespoon}, half the @Cornstarch{1%tablespoon}, half the @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, and 1 TBSP water.

In a medium bowl (use a large bowl for 4 servings), combine @Coleslaw Mix{4%ounce}, @Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon}, lime zest, half the corn, remaining Southwest Spice, juice from remaining lime, and @Sugar{1/4%tsp}. Season generously with @salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Halve and toast @Potato Buns{2}.

While buns toast, heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chopped onion and a pinch of @salt{}; cook, stirring, until softened and translucent, ~{3-5%minutes}. Add garlic and cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @Black Beans{13.4%ounce} and their liquid and sauce. Using the back of a #wooden spoon{} or #spatula{}, roughly mash beans. Cook until beans are warmed through and sauce has thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: Leave some beans whole for texture!

Remove from heat and stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon}. Season with @salt{} and @Pepper{} to taste.

Divide toasted buns between plates; fill with as much filling and pickled onion (draining first) as you like.

> TIP: You may have some filling leftover—serve on the side, with tortilla chips if you have some on hand! Serve messy janes with slaw on the side.